    "name": "Sawangwongse Yawnghwe",
    "slug": "sawangwongse-yawnghwe",
    "url": "https://www.labiennale.org/en/art/2026/sawangwongse-yawnghwe",
    "location": "Central Pavilion / Arsenale 1971, Shan State, Burma Lives in Zutphen, The Netherlands, and Chiang Mai, Thailand",
    "description": "Sawangwongse Yawnghwe’s paintings and sculptures offer an unflinching study of genocidal economies and what brings them into being.People’s Desire(2018) is a six-metre-long installation of 2,500 crudely modelled clay figurines – families among them – that walk or float in boats in a mass exodus. The artist called the Rohingya massacres genocidal as early as 2014, connecting them to the Karen, Kachin and Shan peoples stripped of their land and resources under military rule in the longest civil war in contemporary history. Which Way to Land? An Open Question about Burma’s Fate(2023) andThe Bed of Gold Stream(2024) rework colonial maps and photographs of the Shan minority, reclaiming land, history, resources and even copyright. InThe Prince’s Manual, or: The Complete Idiot’s Guide to Burma Post Coup Revolution(2024), the artist grapples with Myanmar after the 2021 coup, characterised by aerial bombardment, scorched-earth tactics, ethnic armies, and revolutionary struggle. In the twoParallaxcanvases, the artist leaves Burma only to encounter Ukraine, Gaza and the West Bank.The Idiot’s Parallax(2025) reads as a screen, borrowing the colours of coders. It posits decolonisation as a violent event that turns outward force inward, risking self-violence. The revolutionary subject emerges as the product of both the ZONE OF NON-BEING and its violent rupture. —Zasha Colah",
    "image": "https://static.labiennale.org/files/styles/square_thumb/public/arte/2026/600x600/yawnghwe-1.jpg?itok=OG6kFGA0",
    "nameZh": "萨旺翁斯·扬韦",
    "descriptionZh": "Sawangwongse Yawnghwe的绘画和雕塑对种族灭绝经济及其产生的原因进行了一丝不苟的研究。人们的Despe(2018)是2500多米长的仿真粘土雕塑,这些雕塑是大规模出走或漂浮在船上的。艺术家称罗兴亚大屠杀早在2014年就与当代历史上最长的内战中在军事统治下被剥夺的土地和资源的克伦人、克钦人和掸人联系在一起。在两条帕拉克萨克海峡(2023年)和金流地(2024年)重新绘制了掸族的殖民地图和相片,收回了土地、历史、资源甚至版权。在《王子手册》中,即《完全白痴向缅甸后政变指南》(2024年),艺术家在2021年政变后与缅甸进行斗争,其特点是空中轰炸、焦土战术、民族军队和革命斗争。在两次纳克萨克纳克纳瓦斯事件中,艺术家只将缅甸视为向西温特尔沃斯岛(西温特尔沃斯) , 向东温特尔特尔维特尔特尔维特尔特尔特尔特尔特"
